Handbook of Nanobiomedical Research : Fundamentals, Applications and Recent Developments (In 4 Volumes) (Frontiers in Nano Biomedical Research)

by Vladimir Torchilin

This book will consist of 4 volumes containing about 70 chapters covering all the major aspects of the growing area of nanomedicine. Leading scientists from 15 countries will cover all major areas of nanobiomedical research Ã¢â‚¬â€ materials for nanomedicine, application of nanomedicine in therapy of various diseases, use of nanomedicines for diagnostic purposes, technology of nanomedicines, and new trends in nanobiomedical research.

This is the first detailed handbook specifically addressing various aspects of nanobiomedicine. Readers will be treated to cutting-edge research and the newest data from leading researchers in this area.

Readership: Academics, researchers, graduate students and professionals interested in contemporary nanomedicine.
